{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850621861,"sessionID":"ses_2870e36d0ffe4mIUYGl99RSV6W","part":{"id":"prt_d78f207b8001vLvVQJVwWTQ1hS","messageID":"msg_d78f1f97c001b6uvB3u5469cFL","sessionID":"ses_2870e36d0ffe4mIUYGl99RSV6W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775850621842,"end":1775850621859}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850621883,"sessionID":"ses_2870e36d0ffe4mIUYGl99RSV6W","part":{"id":"prt_d78f20380001Vn7c7C9PjIvBSo","messageID":"msg_d78f1f97c001b6uvB3u5469cFL","sessionID":"ses_2870e36d0ffe4mIUYGl99RSV6W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-006\n2: title: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n3: module: pkg/workloadmanager\n4: language: Go\n5: size: M\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-006: Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n9: # Module: pkg/workloadmanager\n10: # Language: Go\n11: # Size: M\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: lifecycle-manager\n21:   description: |\n22:     Implement the Sandbox deletion handler and lifecycle management for the WorkloadManager.\n23:     This includes processing sandbox deletion requests, managing graceful shutdown,\n24:     resource cleanup, and lifecycle state transitions. The handler should integrate\n25:     with the existing HTTP service framework and provide proper lifecycle management\n26:     including idle timeout detection, automatic cleanup, and orphan resource handling.\n27: \n28: # Scope\n29: scope:\n30:   in:\n31:     - Sandbox deletion request handling (DELETE /v1/sandboxes/:id)\n32:     - Graceful shutdown with configurable timeout\n33:     - Resource cleanup (CR, pods, services, ingress)\n34:     - Lifecycle state management (running → terminating → terminated)\n35:     - Idle timeout detection and automatic cleanup\n36:     - Orphan sandbox detection and cleanup\n37:     - Force delete capability\n38:     - Batch deletion support\n39:     - Integration with WorkloadManager service layer\n40:     - Store cleanup on sandbox deletion\n41:   out:\n42:     - Sandbox creation logic (handled in AR-005)\n43:     - Sandbox update/patch operations (separate AR)\n44:     - Sandbox monitoring/metrics (separate AR)\n45:     - Sandbox backup/restore (separate AR)\n46: \n47: # Acceptance Criteria\n48: acceptance:\n49:   - Sandbox deletion request is processed and validated\n50:   - Graceful shutdown with configurable timeout (default 30s)\n51:   - All related resources are properly cleaned up\n52:   - Lifecycle state transitions are tracked correctly\n53:   - Idle timeout triggers automatic cleanup\n54:   - Orphan sandboxes are detected and cleaned up\n55:   - Force delete bypasses graceful shutdown\n56:   - Store records are cleaned up on deletion\n57:   - Integration with existing WorkloadManager HTTP framework\n58:   - Proper error handling and status codes\n59:   - Unit tests achieve >= 80% coverage\n60: \n61: # References\n62: references:\n63:   - AR-005: Sandbox Creation Handler\n64:   - AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n65:   - AR-003: client-go Generated Code\n66:   - AR-002: CRD CodeInterpreter Types\n67:   - AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime Types\n68: \n69: # Estimation\n70: estimation:\n71:   size: M\n72:   story_points: 5\n73:   days: 3\n\n(End of file - total 73 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-006\ntitle: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\nmodule: pkg/workloadmanager\nlanguage: Go\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-006: Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n# Module: pkg/workloadmanager\n# Language: Go\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: lifecycle-manager","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775850621839,"end":1775850621880}}}}
