{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850634105,"sessionID":"ses_2870e36d0ffe4mIUYGl99RSV6W","part":{"id":"prt_d78f22f11001OVil2LgMYP4B14","messageID":"msg_d78f21ed8001GPvWWQUgZMlDO3","sessionID":"ses_2870e36d0ffe4mIUYGl99RSV6W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/design.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 Design: Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-006  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** Medium  \n9: \n10: The Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management component provides comprehensive lifecycle control for sandboxes in the AgentCube system. It handles graceful shutdown, resource cleanup, idle detection, and orphan management while integrating with the WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework (AR-004) and Sandbox Creation Handler (AR-005).\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### High-Level Design\n17: \n18: ```\n19: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n20: │                       External Clients                                       │\n21: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                         │\n22: │  │  Web UI     │  │   CLI Tool  │  │  Agent API  │                         │\n23: │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                         │\n24: └─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘\n25:           │                │                │\n26:           ▼                ▼                ▼\n27: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n28: │                    WorkloadManager HTTP Server (AR-004)                      │\n29: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n30: │  │                         Router Layer                                    │ │\n31: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐ ┌──────────────────────────┐ │ │\n32: │  │  │ /api/v1/sandboxes│ │ /api/v1/sandboxes│ │ /api/v1/sandboxes/:id   │ │ │\n33: │  │  │ DELETE (single) │ │ DELETE (batch)  │ │ DELETE (force)          │ │ │\n34: │  │  └────────┬────────┘ └────────┬────────┘ └───────────┬────────────────┘ │ │\n35: │  └───────────┼───────────────────┼──────────────────────┼──────────────────┘ │\n36: │              │                   │                      │                    │\n37: │  ┌───────────▼───────────────────▼──────────────────────▼──────────────────┐ │\n38: │  │                      Deletion Handler Layer                              │ │\n39: │  │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────┐  │ │\n40: │  │  │ DeleteHandler    │  │ BatchDelete      │  │ ForceDelete          │  │ │\n41: │  │  │ · Validate       │  │ · Filter         │  │ · Skip graceful      │  │ │\n42: │  │  │ · Initiate       │  │ · Parallel       │  │ · Immediate          │  │ │\n43: │  │  └────────┬─────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────┘  │ │\n44: │  └───────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n45: └──────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n46:                │\n47:                ▼\n48: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n49: │                       Lifecycle Manager Layer                                │\n50: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 438. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 Design: Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-006  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Medium  \n\nThe Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management component provides comprehensive lifecycle control for sandboxes in the AgentCube system. It handles graceful shutdown, resource cleanup, idle detection, and orphan management while integrating with the WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework (AR-004) and Sandbox Creation Handler (AR-005).\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                       External Clients                                       │","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/design.md","time":{"start":1775850634090,"end":1775850634103}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850634108,"sessionID":"ses_2870e36d0ffe4mIUYGl99RSV6W","part":{"id":"prt_d78f235a7001MjNRBDMX4vgFNi","messageID":"msg_d78f21ed8001GPvWWQUgZMlDO3","sessionID":"ses_2870e36d0ffe4mIUYGl99RSV6W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Phase 1: Deletion Handler Foundation\n4: \n5: - [ ] Create `DeleteSandbox` handler structure\n6: - [ ] Implement request parsing and validation\n7: - [ ] Add deletion options (graceful, force, timeout)\n8: - [ ] Integrate with AR-004 HTTP framework\n9: \n10: ## Phase 2: Graceful Shutdown Flow\n11: \n12: - [ ] Implement graceful shutdown orchestration\n13: - [ ] Add shutdown timeout handling (default 30s)\n14: - [ ] Implement pre-stop hooks execution\n15: - [ ] Track shutdown progress\n16: \n17: ## Phase 3: Resource Cleanup\n18: \n19: - [ ] Implement CR deletion via dynamic client\n20: - [ ] Add pod cleanup with graceful termination\n21: - [ ] Clean up associated services\n22: - [ ] Clean up ingress resources\n23: - [ ] Handle cleanup failures and retries\n24: \n25: ## Phase 4: Lifecycle State Management\n26: \n27: - [ ] Define lifecycle states (running, terminating, terminated)\n28: - [ ] Implement state transition logic\n29: - [ ] Add state persistence to Store\n30: - [ ] Emit lifecycle events\n31: \n32: ## Phase 5: Idle Timeout Detection\n33: \n34: - [ ] Implement idle timeout checker\n35: - [ ] Track last activity timestamp\n36: - [ ] Add periodic idle scan (interval configurable)\n37: - [ ] Trigger automatic cleanup for idle sandboxes\n38: \n39: ## Phase 6: Orphan Detection\n40: \n41: - [ ] Implement orphan sandbox detector\n42: - [ ] Scan for sandboxes without active sessions\n43: - [ ] Detect sandboxes with missing parent CRs\n44: - [ ] Add cleanup for orphan resources\n45: \n46: ## Phase 7: Batch Operations\n47: \n48: - [ ] Implement batch delete endpoint\n49: - [ ] Add list filter for batch selection\n50: - [ ] Implement parallel deletion with rate limiting\n51: - [ ] Add batch operation status tracking\n52: \n53: ## Phase 8: Store Integration\n54: \n55: - [ ] Update Store interface with deletion methods\n56: - [ ] Implement atomic delete operations\n57: - [ ] Add cascading delete for related records\n58: - [ ] Handle Store consistency on deletion\n59: \n60: ## Phase 9: Error Handling & Recovery\n61: \n62: - [ ] Define deletion error types\n63: - [ ] Implement retry logic for transient failures\n64: - [ ] Add partial failure handling for batch ops\n65: - [ ] Implement cleanup recovery on restart\n66: \n67: ## Phase 10: Testing & Validation\n68: \n69: - [ ] Unit tests for deletion handlers\n70: - [ ] Unit tests for lifecycle manager\n71: - [ ] Integration tests with AR-005 creation\n72: - [ ] Test graceful vs force delete scenarios\n73: - [ ] Verify idle timeout triggers\n74: - [ ] Test orphan cleanup\n75: \n76: ## Checklist\n77: \n78: - [ ] Code follows Go best practices\n79: - [ ] All exported functions have documentation\n80: - [ ] Error handling is consistent\n81: - [ ] Configuration is externalized\n82: - [ ] Tests cover happy path and error cases\n83: - [ ] Integration with AR-004 HTTP framework verified\n84: - [ ] Idle timeout configuration is documented\n85: - [ ] Orphan detection interval is configurable\n\n(End of file - total 85 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase 1: Deletion Handler Foundation\n\n- [ ] Create `DeleteSandbox` handler structure\n- [ ] Implement request parsing and validation\n- [ ] Add deletion options (graceful, force, timeout)\n- [ ] Integrate with AR-004 HTTP framework\n\n## Phase 2: Graceful Shutdown Flow\n\n- [ ] Implement graceful shutdown orchestration\n- [ ] Add shutdown timeout handling (default 30s)\n- [ ] Implement pre-stop hooks execution\n- [ ] Track shutdown progress\n\n## Phase 3: Resource Cleanup\n\n- [ ] Implement CR deletion via dynamic client\n- [ ] Add pod cleanup with graceful termination","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/plan.md","time":{"start":1775850634093,"end":1775850634105}}}}
